article.headline: Cal Poly 74, Sacramento State 65
article.story: SAN LUIS OBISPO, Calif. (AP) -- Derek Stockalper had his third double-double of the season as Cal Poly defeated Sacramento State 74-65 in a nonconference game Tuesday. Stockalper finished with 17 points and 11 rebounds for the Mustangs (8-8). Cal Poly's Tyler McGinn tied Stockalper with a team-high 17 points, hitting 5 of 9 from 3-point range. His late 3 from the left wing sealed the win as the Mustangs led by double digits for much of the second half. Titus Shelton just missed a double-double with 15 points and eight rebounds. Trae Clark added 12 points and three assists for Cal Poly. Haron Hargrave led Sacramento State with 14 points. The Hornets (7-12) shot just 31.1 percent from the floor and missed 16 of its first 17 3-point attempts.
